Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
    private int temperature;
    private boolean isRaining;

    public WeatherSimulator() {
        temperature = 20; // Default starting temperature in Celsius
        isRaining = false; // Default weather condition
    }

    public void setTemperature(int newTemp) {
        temperature = newTemp;
        if (temperature < 5) {
            isRaining = true; // Cold days have a higher chance of rain
        }
    }

    public void simulateStorm() {
        isRaining = true;
        temperature -= 5; // Storms typically reduce the temperature
    }

    public int getTemperature() {
        return temperature;
    }

    public boolean getIsRaining() {
        return isRaining;
    }
}",

If we manually invoke `simulateStorm()`, will this definitively lead to a decrease in temperature?
